News Releases

Payroll employment rises by 379,000 in February; unemployment rate changes little at 6.2% Total nonfarm payroll employment rose by 379,000 in February, and the unemployment rate was little changed at 6.2 percent. The labor market continued to reflect the impact of the coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic.

| | | |

Real average hourly earnings for all employees decrease 0.2% over the month in February Real average hourly earnings for all employees decreased 0.2 percent over the month in February, seasonally adjusted. Average hourly earnings increased 0.2 percent and CPI-U increased 0.4 percent. Real average weekly earnings decreased 1.0 percent over the month.

| |

